India’s Foreign Reserves Rise $5.27 Billion to $317.5 Billion

-- B y   T u s h a r   D h a r a
-- 
2011-10-21T11:30:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/india-s-foreign-reserves-rise-5-27-billion-to-317-5-billion.html
India ’s foreign-exchange reserves
rose $5.27 billion to $317.5 billion in the week ended Oct. 14,
the central bank said.  Foreign-currency assets rose $5.19 billion to $281.7
billion, while the nation’s gold reserves were stable at $28.67
billion in the week, the Mumbai-based Reserve Bank of India said
in an e-mailed statement today.  India’s special drawing rights with the International
Monetary Fund increased $49 million to $4.54 billion while its
reserves with the IMF expanded $29 million to $2.64 billion.
Total reserves climbed by $21.1 billion in the past year, the
bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
